From: slothfulchat <dev@slothfulchat.local>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 02:07:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 49/57] web-app: opaque white background on webxdc navbar app
 icons

The last-used-app icons shown in a chat's title bar are app-supplied,
untrusted images. A transparent icon could be crafted to impersonate a
native navbar control (e.g. a fake three-dot menu) by leaving pixels
transparent where the real icon has them. Give the icon tile an opaque
white background so transparent areas never blend into the navbar; the
tile always reads as a distinct app icon rather than chrome. Their hit
target stays icon-sized (the button keeps padding: 0), unlike the native
navbar buttons.
---
 .../frontend/src/components/ChatView/styles.module.scss  | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/packages/frontend/src/components/ChatView/styles.module.scss b/packages/frontend/src/components/ChatView/styles.module.scss
index 28e5e1045..00b21791f 100644
--- a/packages/frontend/src/components/ChatView/styles.module.scss
+++ b/packages/frontend/src/components/ChatView/styles.module.scss
@@ -96,6 +96,15 @@
     height: 25px;
     cursor: pointer;
     border-radius: 3px;
+    // App-supplied icons are untrusted content. Without a backdrop, an icon
+    // that is transparent where a native navbar control has pixels could be
+    // drawn to impersonate one (e.g. a fake three-dot menu). Force an opaque
+    // white tile so transparent areas never blend into the navbar — the icon
+    // always reads as a distinct app tile, not chrome.
+    background-color: #fff;
+    // Unlike the native navbar buttons, these user-content tiles deliberately
+    // keep a hit target no larger than the icon itself (the button sets
+    // `padding: 0`), so a stray tap can't launch an app.
   }
 }
 
